-- CMD-1.0 Wave C (cont.) — coverage_status (§7.11 operational-honesty metric).
-- Derived by cross-checking companies.airtable_record_id against Airtable link graphs:
--   covered = target of an ACTIVE Automation Registry automation (actually crawling).
--   partial = configured in an automation/RSS feed but not actively crawling (RSS Pipeline
--             Status is 'Not Connected' for ALL 514 feeds — configured, not connected).
--   uncovered = referenced nowhere. Emitted only for the 469 Airtable-curated companies
--   (the crawl graph links Tracking Companies records); roster-only entities are outside
--   this graph entirely and are reported as a structural coverage gap, not stamped here.
-- opposition_exposure (§7.9) is NOT derivable: the Community Opposition Registry
-- (tblJlXwlA4qtimSrG) has no developer/company link field — recorded as a gap, not populated.

